{"key":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01|2Sa|1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","chapter":1,"textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024","parserRevision":"v10","verses":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:1","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":1,"text":"After the death of Saul, David returned from defeating the Amalekites and stayed at Ziklag two days.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:2","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":2,"text":"On the third day a man with torn clothes and dust on his head came from Saul’s camp. When he came to David, he fell to the ground and paid homage.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:3","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":3,"text":"David asked him, “Where have you come from?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:4","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":4,"text":"“What was the outcome? Tell me,” David asked him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:5","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":5,"text":"David asked the young man who had brought him the report, “How do you know Saul and his son Jonathan are dead?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:6","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":6,"text":"“I happened to be on Mount Gilboa,” he replied, “and there was Saul, leaning on his spear. At that very moment the chariots and the cavalry were closing in on him.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:7","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":7,"text":"When he turned around and saw me, he called out to me, so I answered: I’m at your service.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:8","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":8,"text":"He asked me, ‘Who are you?’ I told him: I’m an Amalekite.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:9","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":9,"text":"Then he begged me, ‘Stand over me and kill me, for I’m mortally wounded, but my life still lingers.’","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:10","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":10,"text":"So I stood over him and killed him because I knew that after he had fallen he couldn’t survive. I took the crown that was on his head and the armband that was on his arm, and I’ve brought them here to my lord.”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:11","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":11,"text":"Then David took hold of his clothes and tore them, and all the men with him did the same.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:12","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":12,"text":"They mourned, wept, and fasted until the evening for those who died by the sword —for Saul, his son Jonathan, the Lord’s people, and the house of Israel.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:13","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":13,"text":"David inquired of the young man who had brought him the report, “Where are you from?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:14","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":14,"text":"David questioned him, “How is it that you were not afraid to lift your hand to destroy the Lord’s anointed?”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:15","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":15,"text":"Then David summoned one of his servants and said, “Come here and kill him!” The servant struck him, and he died.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:16","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":16,"text":"For David had said to the Amalekite, “Your blood is on your own head because your own mouth testified against you by saying, ‘I killed the Lord’s anointed.’”","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:17","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":17,"text":"David sang the following lament for Saul and his son Jonathan,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:18","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":18,"text":"and he ordered that the Judahites be taught The Song of the Bow. It is written in the Book of Jashar:","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:19","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":19,"text":"The splendor of Israel lies slain on your heights.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:20","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":20,"text":"Do not tell it in Gath,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:21","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":21,"text":"Mountains of Gilboa,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:22","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":22,"text":"Jonathan’s bow never retreated,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:23","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":23,"text":"Saul and Jonathan,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:24","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":24,"text":"Daughters of Israel, weep for Saul,","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:25","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":25,"text":"How the mighty have fallen in the thick of battle!","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:26","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":26,"text":"I grieve for you, Jonathan, my brother.","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:27","bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","bookOrder":9,"chapter":1,"verse":27,"text":"How the mighty have fallen","textRevision":"api-bible-csb-2024"}],"layout":{"bibleId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01","bookAbbr":"2Sa","chapter":1,"paragraphStarts":[1,4,5,6,11,13,14,17,19,20,21,22,23,24,25,26,27],"headings":[{"beforeVerse":1,"text":"Responses to Saul’s Death"}],"poetryBlocks":[{"beforeVerse":19,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":20,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":21,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":22,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":23,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":24,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":25,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":26,"level":1},{"beforeVerse":27,"level":1}],"studyByVerse":[{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:1","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"After the death of Saul, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 31:1","book":"1Sa","chapter":31,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" David returned from defeating the Amalekites "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 30:1","book":"1Sa","chapter":30,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" and stayed at Ziklag two days. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Sm 31:1","book":"1Sa","chapter":31,"verse":1},{"label":"1Sm 30:1","book":"1Sa","chapter":30,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:2","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"On the third day a man with torn clothes and dust on his head "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jos 7:6","book":"Jos","chapter":7,"verse":6,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 4:12","book":"1Sa","chapter":4,"verse":12,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" came from Saul’s camp. When he came to David, he fell to the ground and paid homage. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jos 7:6","book":"Jos","chapter":7,"verse":6},{"label":"1Sm 4:12","book":"1Sa","chapter":4,"verse":12}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:3","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"David asked him, “Where have you come from?”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:4","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“What was the outcome? Tell me,” David asked him."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:5","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"David asked the young man who had brought him the report, “How do you know Saul and his son Jonathan are dead?”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:6","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"“I happened to be on Mount Gilboa,” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 31:1","book":"1Sa","chapter":31,"verse":1,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Ch 10:1–6","book":"1Ch","chapter":10,"verse":1,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" he replied, “and there was Saul, leaning on his spear. At that very moment the chariots and the cavalry were closing in on him. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Sm 31:1","book":"1Sa","chapter":31,"verse":1},{"label":"1Ch 10:1–6","book":"1Ch","chapter":10,"verse":1}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:7","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"When he turned around and saw me, he called out to me, so I answered: I’m at your service. "}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:8","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"He asked me, ‘Who are you?’ I told him: I’m an Amalekite. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 36:12","book":"Gen","chapter":36,"verse":12,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Gn 36:16","book":"Gen","chapter":36,"verse":16,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ex 17:8–16","book":"Exo","chapter":17,"verse":8,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Nm 24:20","book":"Num","chapter":24,"verse":20,"letter":"d"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Dt 25:19","book":"Deu","chapter":25,"verse":19,"letter":"e"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 15:1","book":"1Sa","chapter":15,"verse":1,"letter":"f"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 30:1–20","book":"1Sa","chapter":30,"verse":1,"letter":"g"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Ch 1:36","book":"1Ch","chapter":1,"verse":36,"letter":"h"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Gn 36:12","book":"Gen","chapter":36,"verse":12},{"label":"Gn 36:16","book":"Gen","chapter":36,"verse":16},{"label":"Ex 17:8–16","book":"Exo","chapter":17,"verse":8},{"label":"Nm 24:20","book":"Num","chapter":24,"verse":20},{"label":"Dt 25:19","book":"Deu","chapter":25,"verse":19},{"label":"1Sm 15:1","book":"1Sa","chapter":15,"verse":1},{"label":"1Sm 30:1–20","book":"1Sa","chapter":30,"verse":1},{"label":"1Ch 1:36","book":"1Ch","chapter":1,"verse":36}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:9","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then he begged me, ‘Stand over me and kill me, for I’m mortally wounded, "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"LXX reads for terrible darkness has taken hold of me"},{"kind":"text","text":" but my life still lingers.’ "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jdg 9:54","book":"Jdg","chapter":9,"verse":54,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jdg 9:54","book":"Jdg","chapter":9,"verse":54}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"LXX reads for terrible darkness has taken hold of me"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:10","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"So I stood over him and killed him because I knew that after he had fallen he couldn’t survive. I took the crown that was on his head and the armband that was on his arm, and I’ve brought them here to my lord.”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:11","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then David took hold of his clothes and tore them, "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jos 7:6","book":"Jos","chapter":7,"verse":6,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Sm 3:31","book":"2Sa","chapter":3,"verse":31,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Sm 13:31","book":"2Sa","chapter":13,"verse":31,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" and all the men with him did the same. "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jos 7:6","book":"Jos","chapter":7,"verse":6},{"label":"2Sm 3:31","book":"2Sa","chapter":3,"verse":31},{"label":"2Sm 13:31","book":"2Sa","chapter":13,"verse":31}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:12","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"They mourned, wept, and fasted until the evening "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Sm 3:35","book":"2Sa","chapter":3,"verse":35,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" for those who died by the sword —for Saul, his son Jonathan, the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"’s people, and the house of Israel."}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Sm 3:35","book":"2Sa","chapter":3,"verse":35}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:13","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"David inquired of the young man who had brought him the report, “Where are you from?”"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:14","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"David questioned him, “How is it that you were not afraid to lift your hand to destroy the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"’s anointed?” "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 24:6","book":"1Sa","chapter":24,"verse":6,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 26:6–12","book":"1Sa","chapter":26,"verse":6,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"1Sm 31:4","book":"1Sa","chapter":31,"verse":4,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"1Sm 24:6","book":"1Sa","chapter":24,"verse":6},{"label":"1Sm 26:6–12","book":"1Sa","chapter":26,"verse":6},{"label":"1Sm 31:4","book":"1Sa","chapter":31,"verse":4}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:15","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Then David summoned one of his servants and said, “Come here and kill him!” The servant struck him, and he died. "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Sm 4:10","book":"2Sa","chapter":4,"verse":10,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"text","text":" "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Sm 4:10","book":"2Sa","chapter":4,"verse":10}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:16","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"For David had said to the Amalekite, “Your blood is on your own head "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jos 2:19","book":"Jos","chapter":2,"verse":19,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Mt 27:24–25","book":"Mat","chapter":27,"verse":24,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Ac 18:5–6","book":"Act","chapter":18,"verse":5,"letter":"c"},{"kind":"text","text":" because your own mouth testified against you by saying, ‘I killed the "},{"kind":"text","text":"Lord","style":"divine"},{"kind":"text","text":"’s anointed.’”"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jos 2:19","book":"Jos","chapter":2,"verse":19},{"label":"Mt 27:24–25","book":"Mat","chapter":27,"verse":24},{"label":"Ac 18:5–6","book":"Act","chapter":18,"verse":5}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:17","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"David sang the following lament "},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Sm 3:33","book":"2Sa","chapter":3,"verse":33,"letter":"a"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"2Ch 35:24–25","book":"2Ch","chapter":35,"verse":24,"letter":"b"},{"kind":"text","text":" for Saul and his son Jonathan, "}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"2Sm 3:33","book":"2Sa","chapter":3,"verse":33},{"label":"2Ch 35:24–25","book":"2Ch","chapter":35,"verse":24}],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:18","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"and he ordered that the Judahites be taught The Song of the Bow. It is written in the Book of Jashar: "},{"kind":"footnote","marker":1,"text":"Or of the Upright"},{"kind":"crossref","label":"Jos 10:12–13","book":"Jos","chapter":10,"verse":12,"letter":"a"}],"crossRefs":[{"label":"Jos 10:12–13","book":"Jos","chapter":10,"verse":12}],"footnotes":[{"marker":1,"text":"Or of the Upright"}]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:19","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"The splendor of Israel lies slain on your heights."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:20","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Do not tell it in Gath,"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:21","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Mountains of Gilboa,"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:22","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Jonathan’s bow never retreated,"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:23","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Saul and Jonathan,"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:24","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"Daughters of Israel, weep for Saul,"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:25","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"How the mighty have fallen in the thick of battle!"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:26","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"I grieve for you, Jonathan, my brother."}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]},{"verseId":"a556c5305ee15c3f-01:2Sa:1:27","parts":[{"kind":"text","text":"How the mighty have fallen"}],"crossRefs":[],"footnotes":[]}]},"cachedAt":1783099295249}